#. type: Title ##
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Packaging philosophy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:11
msgid ""
"The simplicity of using apps is a key feature of YunoHost. As a packager, "
"you should remember these principles:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:13
msgid ""
"**The admin should not have a PhD in computer science to be able to install, "
"configure and use your application**: try to assume that the admin doesn't "
"know about advanced computer concepts;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:15
msgid ""
"**Less is more**, **Keep it simple**: don't overcrowd the admin with a "
"dozens technical questions;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:17
msgid ""
"**Things should work out of the box**: for example, the admin should not "
"have to manually finish the installation process by manually filling in "
"database credentials;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:19
msgid ""
"YunoHost app packaging is **not just about installing** sources and "
"dependencies: it's also about maintenance (upgrade, backup...) and "
"integrating the app in the YunoHost ecosystem (NGINX, SSO/LDAP, Fail2Ban, "
"application catalog, UI/UX...)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "2. Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:23
msgid "Before diving in, this documentation assumes that:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:28
msgid ""
"You already are a YunoHost admin yourself and already know what the install "
"workflow looks like;)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:28
msgid ""
"You are somewhat familiar with (or are willing to learn) system "
"administration and bash programming;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:28
msgid "You are somewhat familiar with (or are willing to learn) Git;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:28
msgid ""
"You are comfortable with tinkering and debugging computer stuff in general."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:30
msgid ""
"You are also encouraged to join the [app packaging chatroom](/community/"
"chat_rooms) to ask any question you may have!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:32
msgid ""
"At some point, you will also want to have a dev/test environment, either "
"using [VirtualBox](/dev/packaging/misc/packaging_apps_virtualbox) or [LXC/"
"ynh-dev](https://github.com/yunohost/ynh-dev) which is meant for the core "
"but can totally be used for developping apps. You can also setup a dev/test "
"VPS on your favourite hosting provider, or even develop on your prod if you "
"like to live dangerously;)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "3. Notes about the history of YunoHost's app packaging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:36
msgid ""
"Many things in YunoHost, and YunoHost app packaging format, are historical "
"or were designed in an organic fashion. Thus some aspects may legitimately "
"feel old."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:38
msgid ""
"The **\"v0\" of app packaging** consisted in writing raw bash scripts with "
"no real standardization/constrain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:40
msgid ""
"Over time, recurrent steps (such as installing dependencies with apt, or "
"setting up the NGINX config) where formalized into standardized bash "
"functions, aka \"helpers\". This pretty much marked **the beginning of the "
"\"v1\" packaging era**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:42
msgid ""
"Various tools were implemented to test the app and standardize their "
"behavior."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:44
msgid ""
"After a while, a set of common practices and conventions emerged and is "
"somewhat reflected and maintain in the [`example_ynh`](https://github.com/"
"YunoHost/example_ynh) template application. While it is tempting for dev-"
"oriented folks to change variable naming schemes or refactorize the "
"structure of scripts, it turns out that it is even more important to stick "
"to the common set of practices (even though arbitrary and not elegant) to "
"ease the maintenance of all apps by any member of the packaging community "
"accross all repos!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:46
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, even though helpers existed, the inherent structure of apps "
"was hard and boring to maintain with too many redundant pieces of code or "
"filled with funky historical conventions. **A new v2 format** [has been "
"designed and added to YunoHost 11.1 in early 2023](https://github.com/"
"YunoHost/yunohost/pull/1289) in the hope to modernize and simplify app "
"packaging and improve the UI/UX of YunoHost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/50.packaging/index.mdx:47
msgid ""
"However, [**a future v3 format** has yet to come](https://github.com/"
"YunoHost/issues/issues/2136) to further simplify app packaging (such as "
"taking care of NGINX/systemd/... configurations, removing the need to "
"manually write remove/backup/restore scripts, etc.)"
msgstr ""
